  "gloss": "Since the Brahmins whom Sri Parasurama first brought to Kerala went back, he — so that the second group would not likewise leave — moved their hair-tuft from the back of the head to the front, changed most of their customs, gave them the name Namboothiris, and settled them permanently in Kerala; and after he vanished from this world at Thrissivaperur in central Kerala, all the Namboothiris together resolved that, for the full prosperity of Kerala, they should go to Kanchipuram, worship Kamakshi Amman until she showed herself, bring her back, and enshrine her in Kerala; and for that purpose they chose and sent the \"Thiruvalayannur\" Bhattathiri, with the \"Keezhottukara\" Namboothiripad and the \"Komarathu\" Menon to assist him.",
